# Use Case 2: Transformations...
created: 2025-07-26, last updated: 2026-06-04, [Read more](https://hookdeck.com/docs/guides/how-to-order-transformations-and-filters)

By default, transformations ran before filters, but you can decide the order that best suits your use case.
...
**Step 1: Create a Filter**
First, create a Filter rule that only allows events with the type `invoice.updated` to pass through.
...
**Step 2: Create a Transformation**
Next, add a Transformation rule *after* the filter.
This transformation script can now safely assume it will only ever receive `invoice.updated` events.
```
addHandler("transform", (request, context) => {
// This logic only runs for "invoice.updated" events
request.body.transformed = true;
// ...perform more specific logic on the invoice payload
return request;
});
```
